In your whole Book you ſeem to ſuppoſe, that the Ʋnity of God was a prime Article of the Pagans Creed: which cap. 7 Sect. 5. I have ſhewed to be falſe. To what I ſaid there, I add out of Origen theſe following Proofs. Lib. 1. cont. Celſ. pag. 5. he ſpeaks of Laws for Idols, and Polytheiſm;
〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 . And p. 28. he ſays, Prophets were given to the Jews, to hinder their falling into Pagans Polytheiſm. And l. 3. p. 155. he ſays, that the Wiſe Men, or Philoſophers, fell from the Cult of One God, into Impious, or Atheiſtical Polytheiſm. He told us in his Firſt Book, pag. 51. that Ariſtotle fled from Athens to Chalcis, to avoid the Fate of Socrates, who had been condemned, for teaching there was but One God. And it is as evident out of Athenagoras,
and others, that Chriſtans were deemed Impious, and Atheiſts, for denying Polytheiſm.
